Convert an alpha numeric Ordnance Survey grid reference to easting and northing or vice versa.

Usage:

  gridref <gridref>
  gridref [--figures=<n>] <coordinate>

When - is passed instead of a <gridref> or <coordinate> read from standard input.

Options:

%s

Examples:

Convert the grid reference for the Tower of London to British National Grid coordinate pair:

    gridref TQ336805

Convert the BNG coordinate pair for the Tower of London to a 6 figure gird reference:

    gridref --figures=6 "533600 180500"

